{"author":{"id":"b61c47ca5a9c68ca888200a05fda3b9b9b90377e8f2b3cfb360b85fce827bec9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1716819827,"nonce":"7tS7Srm9/cH0PX8IkE1D7zGOiAA=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOJl1IZM6KPXv0","github-url":"https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/243","origin":"github"},"title":"Do not automatically delete com.apple.quarantine attribute","message":"The Homebrew installation script automatically removes quarantine as way to make it easier to install and run the application, as stated in the README:\n\n\u003e [Homebrew installation script](https://github.com/nikitabobko/homebrew-tap/blob/main/Casks/aerospace.rb) is configured to automatically delete com.apple.quarantine attribute, that's why the app should work out of the box, without any warnings that \"Apple cannot check AeroSpace for malicious software\"\n\nHowever, while I believe this is a. non-issue for most cases, I also believe it is a bad practice and could be seen as a security risk in some cases (e.g. company approved software).\n\nA much better option would be to explicitly ask the user, at the end of Homebrew installation, if they want to delete com.apple.quarantine attribute, or provide instructions to do it manually.","files":null}]}